Aratasaurus (meaning "lizard born of fire") is a monotypic genus of basal coelurosaurian theropod which includes a single species, Aratasaurus museunacionali, known from fossils found in deposits of the Romualdo Formation in Brazil. Aratasaurus lived during the Albian stage of the Early Cretaceous (111-108 Ma; possibly as early as 115 Ma).The specimen, a juvenile, was estimated to be about 3 metres (9.8 ft) long, and weigh around 34 kilograms (75 lb)

